com.martinandersson.money.benchmark

Class ReadFastMoneyNumberBenchmark

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.martinandersson.money.benchmark.ReadFastMoneyNumberBenchmark

  • public class ReadFastMoneyNumberBenchmark
extends java.lang.Object
    If you'd like to serialize a FastMoney yourself, then getting hold of the internally used long number is probably something you'd wanna do.

    It can be done using public API, or, Java reflection. Question is, which approach is the fastest?

    Fastest on author's machine was reflection (API was almost 4.5 times slower).
